      • LdistanceToCandidates

        public static Candidate LdistanceToCandidates(java.lang.String currentCandidateName)
        Gets the current candidate if the edit distance between the passed candidateName and the Registered Candidate is <=3. Creates a New WriteIn Candidate other wise.
        Parameters:
        currentCandidateName - Name of the candidate whose edit distance must be compared with all the registered candidates.
        Returns:
        the Candidate matching the name if edit distance<=3. Creates a new write in candidate otherwise.

      • LdistanceToCandidatesName

        public static java.lang.String LdistanceToCandidatesName(java.lang.String currentCandidateName)
        Everything is similar to LdistanceToCandidates(String currentCandidateName). Except, instead of returning a Candidate, this returns the corresponding Name that matches.
        Parameters:
        currentCandidateName - Candidate name to be checked for Ldistance.
        Returns:
        matched candidate.

      • mergeMapsAddingIntegerValues

        public static boolean mergeMapsAddingIntegerValues(java.util.Map<Candidate,java.lang.Integer> map1,
                                                   java.util.Map<Candidate,java.lang.Integer> map2)
        Add the key value pairs to the votes, if the key is already added, just update the values, otherwise add newly to the map. If the specified key is not already associated with a value or is associated with null, associates it with the given non-null value. Otherwise, replaces the associated value with the results of the given remapping function, or removes if the result is {null}. This method may be of use when combining multiple mapped values for a key.
        Parameters:
        map1 - iterates through the elements of map1.
        map2 - adds all the values from map1 to map2, maintaining the keys.
        Returns:
        true if merging happened.
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if the null values are passed.
